âœ… Step 6 â€” Write Java Code to Load CSV (15 min)

Create file:

src/main/java/com/darling/ai/Day1CsvLoader.java


Paste this:

package com.darling.ai;

import smile.data.DataFrame;
import smile.io.Read;

import java.nio.file.Paths;

public class Day1CsvLoader {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {

        // Load CSV from resources folder
        var path = Paths.get("src/main/resources/data/students.csv");

        DataFrame df = Read.csv(path.toString());

        System.out.println("=== Dataset Loaded Successfully ===");
        System.out.println("Rows: " + df.nrows());
        System.out.println("Columns: " + df.ncols());

        System.out.println("\n=== First 5 Rows ===");
        System.out.println(df.head(5));
    }
}

âœ… Step 7 â€” Run the Program (5 min)

Right click â†’ Run Day1CsvLoader

You should see output like:

Rows: 6
Columns: 4


and first 5 rows printed.

